The paper discusses the use of natural language processing in software engineering, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper specifically focuses on pre-processing textual information, which involves language features and character tri-grams, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also mentions classification and regression techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper provides a lightweight approach for text analysis, which could be relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
